ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3051.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re</span><hr size=1> offense and defense are both caped at 210 until level 50. then at 51+ they raise again to a max of 252. (ar 59 or 60 if i remember right)<br>
and forget kei or dex or agi buffs and all that, they will cap out anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abividad>Abividad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/03 12:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3051.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Re</span><hr size=1> FYI After 51 you can raise offense, defense and weapon skills 5 points per level. Not sure what max kick, bash disarm raises were necause I didn't have them maxed beforehand. Taunt, riposte, and parry, have only gone up 3 points per level for me, and at 53 I'm still at 217 double attack and 222 dual wield, though admittedly I have not done a ton of dual wielding, just enough to get 1hs maxed at 215 and 1hb to 214 <p><img name="Sig5" src="http://users.conwaycorp.net/vanessa/Sig5.jpg" width="400" height="188" border="0" usemap="#m_Sig5"> 
